#resources
  %p
    This area is used to notify EOL of a resource (i.e. data set) that is available for processing and
    entry in the EOL database.  You can either upload
    your resource or place it on a public server and indicate its URL.  Currently, the resource files you provide must be in
    the
    = link_to 'EOL Transfer Schema format',:controller=>'content_partner',:action=>'transfer_overview'
    \.
  %p
    Use the 'Force' action to force your resource to be harvested tonight, regardless of its normal schedule. Note that you do not need to use this option when you first create your resource--it will be harvested tonight by default.
  - if current_objects.empty?
    %p
      You currently have no resources described.
  - else
    %table{ :width => "100%" }
      %tr.resources_table_head
        %th
          Title
        %th
          Dataset URL
        %th
          Frequency
        %th
          License
        %th
          Status
        %th
          Actions
        %th
          RSS status
      - for resource in @resources
        %tr{ :class => resource.description.blank? ? 'class="resource_rowsep"' : '' }
          %td
            = link_to h(resource.title), resource_harvest_events_url(resource)
            - if h = resource.hierarchy
              %br
              %small
                = "("+ link_to('see taxa in this resource', { :controller => 'content_partner', :action => 'hierarchy', :id => h.id })+")"
          %td
            - dataset_url = resource.accesspoint_url.blank? ? resource.dataset_file_name : resource.accesspoint_url
            - unless dataset_url.blank?
              = link_to(dataset_url.sub(/^.*\//, ''), dataset_url, :alt => dataset_url)
          %td{ :align => "center" }
            = h frequency(resource.refresh_period_hours)
          %td
            = h (resource.license.blank? ? "unspecified" : resource.license.title)
          %td
            %span{ :id => "status_#{resource.id}" }
              = h resource.status_label
          %td
            %span><= link_to 'Edit', edit_resource_path(resource)
            \&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
            %span><= link_to_remote 'Force', :url => force_harvest_resource_path(resource), :method => :post, :update => "status_#{resource.id}", :confirm => 'Are you sure you want this resource harvested tonight?'

          %td
            = link_to(image_tag('rss.png',:alt=>'rss',:title=>'rss'), "http://services.eol.org/RSS_resource_monitor/process.php?f=5&resources_id=#{resource.id}")
        - if !resource.description.blank?
          %tr.resource_rowsep
            %td.resource_indented{ :colspan => "8" }
              %b
                Description:
              = h resource.description
  %br
  = link_to 'Create a new resource description', new_resource_path
